WEBVTT

00:17.350 --> 00:19.561
I take care of him
every single day.

00:19.644 --> 00:22.564
All day long. And you're gonna bawl me out
for one night with my friends?

00:22.647 --> 00:23.565
You think I'm stupid?

00:23.648 --> 00:26.651
-You think I'm gonna believe this shit?
-No. I think you're paranoid.

00:27.193 --> 00:28.319
You need help.

00:28.403 --> 00:30.030
I'm not done talking to you.

00:30.155 --> 00:32.282
- Don't touch me!
-Or what? What are you gonna do?

00:32.365 --> 00:34.576
- Let go of me. You're hurting me.
-You think I'm a fool?

00:34.659 --> 00:35.869
Is that what you think of me?

00:35.952 --> 00:38.163
-Why can't you just do right...
-No, please!

00:38.246 --> 00:40.081
...and love me
like you're supposed to, huh?

00:44.169 --> 00:47.797
<i> It's been said</i>
<i>that dreams are illustrations</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:50.800
<i>from the book</i>
<i>your soul is writing about you.</i>

00:51.009 --> 00:53.845
<i>So why do I keep dreaming</i>
<i>about my childhood?</i>

00:54.471 --> 00:57.348
<i>Dr. Nicky would have said</i>
<i>I have unprocessed feelings</i>

00:57.432 --> 01:00.852
<i>about how my parents</i>
<i>didn't take very good care of me.</i>

01:01.936 --> 01:03.313
<i>But now you do.</i>

01:03.813 --> 01:05.815
<i>In so many ways.</i>

01:09.486 --> 01:10.445
Hey, you.

01:10.987 --> 01:12.822
<i> You make me kinder,</i>

01:13.198 --> 01:14.449
<i>more selfless.</i>

01:15.700 --> 01:17.118
<i>You make me feel good.</i>

01:17.827 --> 01:22.707
<i>So good, I forget whatever darkness</i>
<i>resurfaced in my sleep.</i>

01:22.957 --> 01:25.418
<i>I lose myself in you,</i>

01:25.502 --> 01:27.754
<i>find myself through you,</i>

01:27.837 --> 01:29.297
<i>and when I'm with you,</i>

01:29.380 --> 01:33.134
<i>we're the only two people on Earth.</i>

01:40.475 --> 01:41.434
It's Forty.

01:41.976 --> 01:43.269
Can that wait?

01:43.353 --> 01:45.480
No, I ignored him three times last night.

01:45.855 --> 01:47.273
Okay. Hey.

01:47.732 --> 01:49.776
Lovey, where you been?

01:49.984 --> 01:51.778
<i>Uh, Phone died. What's up?</i>

01:51.861 --> 01:53.488
Ted Hope is what's up.

01:53.738 --> 01:55.406
<i>Ran into him at NeueHouse.</i>

01:55.490 --> 01:59.119
<i>Told him I am this close</i>
<i>to attaching Hendy to my new project,</i>

01:59.202 --> 02:01.579
and he wants to see the full pitch.

02:02.038 --> 02:03.915
Can you even process that?

02:04.374 --> 02:05.250
That's great.

02:05.875 --> 02:07.335
That's really great.

02:07.585 --> 02:11.047
Now all I need to do is mind meld
with our idea machine, Will.

02:11.840 --> 02:13.341
You haven't heard from him, have you?

02:13.424 --> 02:15.009
He... um... hmm.

02:15.135 --> 02:17.137
Yeah, you know,
I haven't heard much from him.

02:17.220 --> 02:19.764
<i>The guy must really not be feeling well.</i>

02:19.848 --> 02:22.142
Yeah, poor guy. Oh.

02:22.684 --> 02:23.601
One other thing.

02:23.852 --> 02:26.312
My inner Sasquatch is coming out,

02:26.396 --> 02:29.691
so I'm gonna need you
to, uh, cut my hair before this meeting.

02:29.774 --> 02:31.109
Yeah, okay. Tomorrow afternoon?

02:31.192 --> 02:33.736
Yeah. Uh, why do you sound
so out of breath?

02:33.820 --> 02:35.947
I'm on the elliptical, you know. Gotta go.

02:38.658 --> 02:41.911
<i> Old me would be annoyed</i>
<i>by such an intrusion.</i>

02:42.370 --> 02:43.663
<i>But new me</i>

02:43.746 --> 02:46.541
<i>-wasn't even fazed by it.</i>

02:46.624 --> 02:49.127
-<i> And you know why that is.</i>
-Oh, right there!

02:49.210 --> 02:51.254
<i>Because I finally feel</i>

02:51.337 --> 02:53.965
<i>like I'm becoming a better man.</i>

02:55.383 --> 02:56.551
That's so fucking good!

02:56.634 --> 02:59.179
<i> And it's all because of you.</i>

03:14.319 --> 03:16.738
Didn't peg you for an outer space guy.

03:18.198 --> 03:19.574
Oh, it came with the apartment.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.910
Along with the pink, fuzzy pillows.

03:22.660 --> 03:25.622
Hey, you can see my house from here.

03:27.290 --> 03:28.750
-All the better to spy on you.

03:28.833 --> 03:31.544
<i> Not that I've needed to</i>
<i>since I trust you completely.</i>

03:40.053 --> 03:41.137
Let me guess.

03:41.512 --> 03:42.347
Forty?

03:42.764 --> 03:44.390
When you text him back just...

03:44.974 --> 03:46.184
don't tell him about us.

03:46.517 --> 03:49.562
<i>But if your brother knew about us,</i>
<i>maybe he'd give us some space.</i>

03:49.646 --> 03:51.272
Remind me again...

03:51.940 --> 03:54.025
why "us" is a secret.

03:54.359 --> 03:57.070
Whenever I start dating someone,

03:57.362 --> 04:00.365
Forty tends to feel threatened.

04:00.448 --> 04:02.533
You know, he doesn't have
many people to count on

04:02.617 --> 04:03.952
so he needs me.

04:04.035 --> 04:07.247
And his sobriety is always
the most fragile in the first...

04:07.497 --> 04:09.457
you know, right after he's slipped.

04:09.999 --> 04:11.834
Let's just give him a week or two

04:12.126 --> 04:13.503
before we, you know,

04:13.878 --> 04:16.506
shove our euphoria in his face.

04:17.382 --> 04:19.384
<i> Even your empathy is a turn-on.</i>

04:20.093 --> 04:21.970
If you're euphoric now, just wait,

04:22.262 --> 04:23.972
just wait until Santa Barbara
this weekend.

04:24.055 --> 04:25.098
I know.

04:32.063 --> 04:34.315
<i> And there goes Santa Barbara.</i>

04:34.941 --> 04:35.900
What if...

04:38.695 --> 04:40.238
we take a rain check

04:40.655 --> 04:41.823
on Santa Barbara?

04:42.240 --> 04:46.369
The more time you spend with him now,
the cooler he'll be when we do tell him.

04:49.122 --> 04:50.748
<i> Anything for you, Love.</i>

04:56.212 --> 04:57.505
I'm seeing him tomorrow night.

04:57.588 --> 04:58.423
Okay.

05:00.466 --> 05:02.844
Well, I guess that means
we'll have to make up for that

05:02.927 --> 05:04.971
lost Santa Barbara sex some other way.

05:16.482 --> 05:19.902
<i> So, this is what it feels like</i>
<i>to be nourished and at peace.</i>

05:20.111 --> 05:22.196
Um what do you think you're doing?

05:22.280 --> 05:23.698
Working on a project?

05:23.781 --> 05:24.991
What project?

05:25.700 --> 05:27.118
I told you, I don't want--

05:27.201 --> 05:29.037
I'm not hanging out
with Henderson anymore.

05:31.414 --> 05:32.707
Why? What'd he do?

05:33.166 --> 05:35.126
He just drinks too much.
It's embarrassing.

05:35.626 --> 05:39.005
<i> This explains why she hasn't</i>
<i>been texting Henderson all week.</i>

05:39.339 --> 05:40.423
<i>Huge relief.</i>

05:40.631 --> 05:42.258
Goetz's dad's girlfriend needs a PA

05:42.342 --> 05:43.968
for a short that starts shooting
next week.

05:44.052 --> 05:47.013
Painfully derivative,
but a credit's a credit.

05:47.680 --> 05:48.681
Till then,

05:49.057 --> 05:51.184
I'm expressing myself through collage.

05:51.267 --> 05:54.187
<i> I never thought I'd say this,</i>
<i>but I feel for Delilah.</i>

05:54.270 --> 05:57.148
<i>She's only trying to protect her sister</i>
<i>from the same sleazeball</i>

05:57.231 --> 05:58.608
<i>she fell victim to.</i>

05:58.858 --> 06:01.277
Just... do not ruin my walls.

06:05.907 --> 06:07.825
Yeah, she so wants to be at power top.

06:07.909 --> 06:08.993
-Tell me about it.
-Mm-hmm.

06:09.285 --> 06:11.329
Can you believe she put
that spy software on my phone?

06:11.412 --> 06:12.288
<i> Shit.</i>

06:12.997 --> 06:14.957
-You sure it was her?
-Who else would it be?

06:15.291 --> 06:17.627
So you're not gonna tell her you know?

06:18.544 --> 06:19.629
Obviously not.

06:20.671 --> 06:23.758
